{"parse":{"title":"greeting","pageid":69835,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{surf|en|greet|-ing}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɡɹiːtɪŋ/}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-greeting.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iːtɪŋ|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# A [[conventional]] phrase used to start a [[letter]] or [[conversation]] or otherwise to acknowledge a person's [[arrival]] or [[presence]].\n#: {{ux|en|It's polite to begin a letter with a '''greeting''', but this practice is less common in email.}}\n#: {{ux|en|[[thank you|Thank you]] to everyone who sent me birthday '''greeting'''s.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Send my '''greeting'''s to your family.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The action of the verb ''to greet''.\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=2|passage=I had occasion […] to make a somewhat long business trip to Chicago, and on my return […] I found Farrar awaiting me in the railway station. He smiled his wonted fraction by way of '''greeting''', […], and finally leading me to his buggy, turned and drove out of town.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|greeting card\n|greetingless\n|greetingly\n|greetings card\n|nongreeting\n|season's greetings\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|greet}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|acknowledgement of a persons presence or arrival}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|përshëndetje|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|تَحِيَّة|f}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|բարև}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|ওলগ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|təbrik}}, {{t+|az|salam}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|прывіта́нне|n}}, {{t+|be|віта́нне|n}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|সালাম}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|по́здрав|m}}, {{t+|bg|приве́тствие|n}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|ပဋိသန္ဒါရစကား}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|salut|m}}, {{t+|ca|salutació|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|迎接|tr=yíngjiē}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|pozdrav|m}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hilsen|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|begroeting|f}}, {{t+|nl|groet|m}}\n* Egyptian: {{t-egy|njnj|h=n:y-n:y-A85}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|saluto}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|tervitus}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|heilsa|f}}, {{t|fo|heilsan|f}}, {{t|fo|kvøða|f}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|tervehdys}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|salutation|f}}, {{t+|fr|salut|m}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|begroeting|c}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|მისალმება}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Gruß|m}}, {{t+|de|Begrüßung|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|χαιρετισμός|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἀσπασμός|m}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|अभिवादन|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|üdvözlet}}, {{t+|hu|köszöntés}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|kveðja|f}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|saluto}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|saluto|m}}, {{t+|it|benvenuto|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|挨拶|tr=あいさつ, aisatsu}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|сәлемдесу}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|បច្ចុគ្គមន៍}}, {{t+|km|ស្វាគមន៍}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|인사(人事)}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|саламдашуу}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|salūtātiō|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|sveiciens|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|pasveikinimas|m}}\n* Luganda: {{t|lg|okubuuza}}, {{t|lg|okulamusa}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|Begréissung|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|поздрав|m}}, {{t|mk|поздравување|n}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|ucapan}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|waioha}}, {{t|mi|mānawa}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|мэндчилгээ}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|hilsen|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t+|nn|helsing}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|پیشواز|tr=pišvâz}}, {{t+|fa|تبریک|tr=tabrik}}, {{t+|fa|سلام|tr=salâm}}, {{t+|fa|احوال‌پرسی|tr=ahvâl-porsi}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Gruss|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|pozdrowienie|n}}, {{t+|pl|powitanie|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|saudação|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|salut|n}}, {{t+|ro|salutare|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|приве́тствие|n}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|fàilte|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|по̏здра̄в|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|pȍzdrāv|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|pozdrav|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|pozdrav}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|saludo|m}}, {{t+|es|salutación|f}}, {{t+|es|saludación|f}} {{qualifier|rare}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|salamu}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hälsning|c}}, {{t+|sv|hälsningsfras}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|pagbati}}, {{t|tl|bati}}, {{t|tl|saludo}}, {{t|tl|pugay}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|табрик}}, {{t|tg|салом}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|การทักทาย}}\n* Tibetan: {{t-needed|bo}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|tebrik}}, {{t+|tr|selam}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|віта́ння|n}}, {{t|uk|привіта́ння|n}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|tabrik}}, {{t|uz|salomlashish}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|chào|alt=lời chào}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|glid}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|cyfarchiad|m}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|גרוס}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|selam}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|en|hello}}\n* {{l|en|salutation}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|en|greet||ing-form}}"}}